{"body": [{"indent": 0, "text": ["SSS Single"], "type": "title", "extent": [48, 63], "level": 0}, {"indent": 0, "type": "summary", "extent": [63, 129], "text": ["A simple implementation of single sub-surface scattering."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [165, 248], "text": ["How much the sub-surface scattering should contribute to the resulting color."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Surface Intensity"], "role": "item", "extent": [141, 165], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [266, 314], "text": ["The color of the sub-surface material."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Subsurface Color"], "role": "item", "extent": [248, 266], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [335, 381], "text": ["The index of refraction of the material."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Index of Refraction"], "role": "item", "extent": [314, 335], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [406, 501], "text": ["When this checkbox is turned on, each wavelength of light will be computed independently."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Evaluate RGB Separately"], "role": "item", "extent": [381, 406], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [518, 771], "text": ["The SSS computation is quite expensive to compute. Both the multi and single scattering VOPs can use point clouds to both improve efficiency and to store intermediate results (caching). This is the name of the file containing the point cloud file."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Pointcloud File"], "role": "item", "extent": [501, 518], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [789, 887], "text": ["The number of neighboring points in the point cloud file to consider when computing the SSS."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Points to Filter"], "role": "item", "extent": [771, 789], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [908, 1076], "text": ["The maximum distance from the shading point to be considered for contribution to the SSS color. This is used both by the point cloud filtering and by ray-tracing."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Scattering Distance"], "role": "item", "extent": [887, 908], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [1094, 1173], "text": ["The scattering phase passed to the Henyey-Greenstein scattering function."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Scattering Phase"], "role": "item", "extent": [1076, 1094], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [1192, 1323], "text": ["The number of samples to use to evaluate the SSS. Increasing this will improve the quality but at greater computational cost."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Number of Samples"], "role": "item", "extent": [1173, 1192], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [1335, 1356], "text": ["Ray-tracing bias."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Trace Bias"], "role": "item", "extent": [1323, 1335], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "parameters_item_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 1, "text": "Parameters", "role": "section", "extent": [129, 141], "container": true, "type": "parameters_section", "id": "parameters"}], "summary": ["A simple implementation of single sub-surface scattering."], "type": "root", "attrs": {"namespace": null, "internal": "singleSSS", "type": "node", "version": null, "context": "vop"}, "title": ["SSS Single"]}